### Game of Life API Test Requests

# IMPORTANT: Execute requests in order!
# 1. First run the "uploadBoard" request to create a board
# 2. Set the value of boardId as a variable in this file below
# 3. All GET requests will automatically use the stored boardId


### 1. Upload Board State
# @name uploadBoard
# This automatically stores the boardId from the response
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/GameOfLife/upload
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rows": 3,
  "columns": 3,
  "grid": [
    [false, true, false],
    [false, true, false],
    [false, true, false]
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("boardId", response.body.boardId);
%}

### 2. Get Next State (automatically uses stored boardId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/GameOfLife/{{boardId}}/next

### 3. Get N States Ahead (e.g., 5 generations)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/GameOfLife/{{boardId}}/advance/5

### 4. Get Final State
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/GameOfLife/{{boardId}}/final

### Example: Blinker Pattern (Oscillator)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/GameOfLife/upload
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rows": 5,
  "columns": 5,
  "grid": [
    [false, false, false, false, false],
    [false, false, true, false, false],
    [false, false, true, false, false],
    [false, false, true, false, false],
    [false, false, false, false, false]
  ]
}

### Example: Block Pattern (Still Life)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/GameOfLife/upload
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rows": 4,
  "columns": 4,
  "grid": [
    [false, false, false, false],
    [false, true, true, false],
    [false, true, true, false],
    [false, false, false, false]
  ]
}

